old school projects.

00:09.052 --> 00:11.359
I remember staying
up all night

00:11.402 --> 00:13.448
helping Malcolm build
this volcano.

00:13.491 --> 00:16.364
You know we even got spaghetti
sauce to shoot out the top?

00:16.407 --> 00:18.148
Aw, I remember.

00:18.192 --> 00:21.543
And Marty scraped it
off the walls with garlic bread.

00:21.586 --> 00:24.241
Those were some good
memories, weren't they?

00:24.285 --> 00:25.329
Yeah.
Real good memories.

00:25.373 --> 00:28.680
Ah, it's trash.

00:28.724 --> 00:30.856
How could you just
throw that away?

00:30.900 --> 00:32.684
Those were some special memories
of Malcolm.

00:32.728 --> 00:34.077
Why we need memories?

00:34.121 --> 00:36.645
The real thing is laying
on our couch right now.

00:38.603 --> 00:39.778
Ha ha!

00:39.822 --> 00:41.476
Look at this, baby,
my old beeper.

00:41.519 --> 00:44.435
You know, I remember
when you used to blow me up

00:44.479 --> 00:48.135
whenever you wanted
a little late-night booty call.

00:48.178 --> 00:49.745
I never had your beeper number.

00:51.442 --> 00:53.618
Well, look at that. You know
what? This ain't even my beeper.

00:54.663 --> 00:57.274
Trash. Yep. Let's go.

00:59.059 --> 01:01.365
Ooh, ahoy, Captain Calvin!

01:01.409 --> 01:03.367
Hey, Dave.

01:03.411 --> 01:04.977
Just getting my daily steps in.

01:05.021 --> 01:07.763
Well, you can get in a bunch
more if you just keep walking.

01:09.808 --> 01:12.333
You know, I am actually
a few steps short.

01:12.376 --> 01:13.725
Good.

01:16.815 --> 01:18.121
Uh, Dave, Dave, Dave, stop that.

01:18.165 --> 01:19.688
You're making me dizzy.
Stop circling me.

01:19.731 --> 01:21.037
Yeah, no problem.
I'll go the other way.

01:23.909 --> 01:25.476
Whoa.

01:25.520 --> 01:26.825
You throwing
all this stuff out?

01:26.869 --> 01:28.958
Yeah, it's just
a bunch of trash.

01:29.001 --> 01:31.265
Well, maybe to you,
but not to everyone.

01:31.308 --> 01:32.614
You know what?

01:32.657 --> 01:33.919
You should have a yard sale.

01:33.963 --> 01:35.530
A yard sale?

01:35.573 --> 01:36.966
In this neighborhood?
I don't think so.

01:37.009 --> 01:39.403
Why, what's wrong
with our neighborhood?

01:39.447 --> 01:41.884
Oh, nothing. Nothing. There's
a lot of good people here.

01:41.927 --> 01:44.104
You know, hardworking,
God-fearing,

01:44.147 --> 01:45.975
and I wouldn't trust
a single one of them.

01:47.542 --> 01:49.152
