13:55.269 --> 13:57.749
Now, she was a real
piece of work.

13:57.793 --> 14:00.056
She was...

14:00.100 --> 14:04.321
but they grew to
respect each other in the end.

14:04.365 --> 14:07.803
That sounds just like that movie
Driving Miss Daisy.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.805
Really?

14:09.849 --> 14:11.372
I never seen it.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.767
At any rate, I'm, uh...

14:15.811 --> 14:18.727
I'm willing to buy
the angel back...

14:18.770 --> 14:19.815
for $20.

14:19.859 --> 14:23.210
$20? Good.
I'll get it for you.

14:23.253 --> 14:24.820
Okay.

14:26.169 --> 14:27.388
Good.

14:27.431 --> 14:29.912
I cannot believe
that you lied to her.

14:29.956 --> 14:33.133
I know. I've seen that
movie, like, three times.

14:35.352 --> 14:38.225
Okay, so Dad gets half.

14:38.268 --> 14:41.576
Which means we get to
split the rest.

14:41.619 --> 14:44.796
This is not
a bad Saturday.

14:44.840 --> 14:47.451
I mean, I can almost
pay Mom and Dad some rent.

14:47.495 --> 14:49.758
I'm not.

14:49.801 --> 14:51.847
But I could.

14:51.891 --> 14:53.936
And, Grover, here is a whole

14:53.980 --> 14:56.243
ten dollars.MALCOLM: Yeah, hey, little man,

14:56.286 --> 14:58.810
we could not have
done this without you.Yeah.

14:58.854 --> 15:01.813
I know, which is why
I want more.

15:01.857 --> 15:04.120
Uh, more?

15:04.164 --> 15:05.556
Yeah, like, how much more?

15:05.600 --> 15:07.471
Uh, 50 sounds good.

15:07.515 --> 15:10.257
What?
Are you out of your
rabbit-ass mind?!

15:10.300 --> 15:12.215
I sold everything
you told me to.

15:12.259 --> 15:16.524
I even let those old ladies mess
my hair and pinch my cheeks.

15:16.567 --> 15:18.439
And you think that's
worth $50?

15:18.482 --> 15:21.746
I pretended to be blindfor you.

15:23.052 --> 15:24.793
Malcolm, pay the boy.

15:26.751 --> 15:27.970
Nice try.

15:28.014 --> 15:29.754
This one's Canadian.

15:31.931 --> 15:34.324
Well, that was
one hell of a mess.

15:34.368 --> 15:35.847
Oh, you should have
tried cleaning it up

15:35.891 --> 15:38.198
with the super-absorbent
Sponge-O-Matic.

15:38.241 --> 15:40.635
I did, but after one minute
it started to burn.

15:40.678 --> 15:42.245
I think my thumbprints are gone.

15:42.289 --> 15:44.465
Ugh.
You know,

15:44.508 --> 15:46.336
I hate to say it,
but Calvin was right.

15:46.380 --> 15:48.773
I don't know why I was
so determined to hold on

15:48.817 --> 15:49.774
to all that junk.

15:49.818 --> 15:51.559
Don't beat yourself
up about it.

15:51.602 --> 15:53.691
You're not the only one
who holds on to stuff.

15:54.823 --> 15:56.781
Damn, that's one ugly-ass baby!

15:58.392 --> 16:00.002
Hey, that's Grover.

16:02.874 --> 16:05.834
I paid an artist on Etsy
to capture him on a plate.

16:05.877 --> 16:08.576
You actually spent money
on a Grover plate?

16:08.619 --> 16:14.582
No. I spent money on
a complete setof Grover plates.

16:14.625 --> 16:17.672
Oh, Gemma, these are bad.

16:17.715 --> 16:18.716
I mean,
these are really bad.

16:18.760 --> 16:20.936
Yeah, I know.

16:20.980 --> 16:22.938
Well, you know what it's like
when you're a new mom.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.374
You're sleep-deprived.

16:24.418 --> 16:26.681
I would just order stuff
on Etsy and eBay.

16:26.724 --> 16:29.118
Yeah, I bought all that stuff
off those infomercials

16:29.162 --> 16:31.555
doing my late-night feedings
with my boys.

16:31.599 --> 16:33.993
Oh, man, those first
few months were so brutal.

16:34.036 --> 16:35.777
Ugh.I was exhausted all the time.

16:35.820 --> 16:37.692
Constantly changing diapers.

16:37.735 --> 16:39.346
Covered in spit-up.

16:39.389 --> 16:40.738
It never stopped.

16:40.782 --> 16:42.914
I am so glad that's all
behind me.

16:42.958 --> 16:43.915
So am I.

16:43.959 --> 16:45.961
But, God, I miss it.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.963
Me, too.

16:48.007 --> 16:51.793
He may have looked like this,
but he smelled like heaven.

16:51.836 --> 16:53.186
Oh... And I miss

16:53.229 --> 16:55.710
Marty and Malcolm's
little toes.
Oh...

16:55.753 --> 16:57.755
Now they just have big,
smelly man feet.

16:57.799 --> 16:58.930
Mm.

16:58.974 --> 17:01.020
You know,

17:01.063 --> 17:03.413
maybe I kept all that kitchen
crap because it connects me

17:03.457 --> 17:04.980
to when the boys were little.

17:05.024 --> 17:07.200
Maybe that's why I can't
bring myself to get rid of

17:07.243 --> 17:08.723
these ceramic nightmares.

17:09.767 --> 17:11.769
What's up, ladies?

17:13.728 --> 17:16.296
Anyone wanna see me
make it rain?

17:17.819 --> 17:19.603
Grover!

17:19.647 --> 17:22.867
What...?Oh, no.

17:22.911 --> 17:23.999
You know what?

17:24.043 --> 17:25.827
You might want to have
another one

17:25.870 --> 17:27.263
just in case that one goes bad.

17:30.832 --> 17:33.791
I see you looking
at me, Dave.

17:33.835 --> 17:35.445
And it's not gonna work.

17:35.489 --> 17:37.882
I've already forgiven me.

17:41.147 --> 17:43.236
You know what, Calvin,
you were right.

17:43.279 --> 17:46.674
This neighborhood is full
of scammers and slicksters.

17:46.717 --> 17:49.807
And I'm looking at
the biggest one right now.

17:49.851 --> 17:52.854
I'm sorry, did you
say something?

17:52.897 --> 17:56.597
I was already spending
my angel money in my head.

17:58.512 --> 18:01.732
Well, you know, since I'm
a part of this neighborhood now,

18:01.776 --> 18:03.691
I'm gonna get in on the action.

18:06.781 --> 18:08.043
What are you doing?

18:08.087 --> 18:11.786
I'm stealing from her,
like I learned from you.

18:13.875 --> 18:15.050
Come on, man, put it back.

18:15.094 --> 18:17.008
No. You know what,
as a matter of fact,

18:17.052 --> 18:19.315
I'm taking this
remote control, too.

18:19.359 --> 18:23.145
Have fun standing up to change
your channels, old lady.

18:23.189 --> 18:24.929
Look, stop playing, man.

18:24.973 --> 18:27.367
Old ladies keep guns.

18:27.410 --> 18:30.370
Give it here. Hey...

18:30.413 --> 18:32.241
What the hell are y'all doing?

18:33.895 --> 18:35.418
Oh, nothing.

18:35.462 --> 18:36.898
What's that in your pocket?

18:38.726 --> 18:41.555
Nothing.

18:41.598 --> 18:43.557
Are you trying to steal
from me?

18:43.600 --> 18:46.908
That's it, I'm calling
my grandson Jay-Bo.

18:49.084 --> 18:50.564
He's only got one strike.

18:50.607 --> 18:53.088
Whoa.

18:53.132 --> 18:54.611
Please, please don't do that.

18:54.655 --> 18:58.789
Look, he was only trying to
get me to do the right thing

18:58.833 --> 19:02.228
and tell you that that angel...

19:02.271 --> 19:05.100
was a valuable antique
worth $1,500.

19:05.144 --> 19:09.148
Yes, and he has seen Driving Miss Daisy.

19:11.019 --> 19:12.977
$1,500?

19:13.021 --> 19:16.894
Yeah. Look, sorry for not
being up front with you,

19:16.938 --> 19:20.681
but... seeing
that I have now,

19:20.724 --> 19:24.250
because I'm a good person,

19:24.293 --> 19:25.903
what do you say
we split it?

19:25.947 --> 19:29.211
Well, $750 is a lot of money.

19:29.255 --> 19:30.952
It sure is.

19:30.995 --> 19:32.867
Now, would you see that.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.260
When you give people
the chance...

19:34.303 --> 19:37.350
But $1,500 is a lot more.

19:40.266 --> 19:41.789
Now, y'all get up out of here.

19:41.832 --> 19:42.920
What?
What?

19:42.964 --> 19:44.183
You heard me, beat it.

19:44.226 --> 19:46.968
But, Miss Simpson,
he just told you the truth.

19:47.011 --> 19:48.970
I know, and that's why
I'm giving you

19:49.013 --> 19:52.191
a five-second head start
before I get my pistol.

19:52.234 --> 19:55.281
Okay, hold--
But, Miss Simpson,

19:55.324 --> 19:57.587
I think...Four, three...

19:57.631 --> 20:00.416
Okay, Dave, let's go.
Go, go, go, go, go!

20:08.163 --> 20:10.034
I feel like a fool.

20:10.078 --> 20:12.689
I'm listening.

20:12.733 --> 20:14.604
I honestly thought
if we told her the truth,

20:14.648 --> 20:16.867
that she would do
the right thing.

20:16.911 --> 20:19.087
Well, actually, she did
do the right thing.

20:19.130 --> 20:20.741
I mean, in this
neighborhood,

20:20.784 --> 20:24.135
a five-second head start
is verygenerous.

20:24.179 --> 20:26.964
Well, you know, maybe
she really needed the money.

20:27.008 --> 20:29.706
For medicine, food, rent.

20:29.750 --> 20:31.491
Keep dreaming, Dave.

20:31.534 --> 20:33.188
Because come Sunday,

20:33.232 --> 20:34.929
she is on a church
bus to Vegas.

20:36.539 --> 20:40.195
Well, you know, in that case,
I don't feel so bad.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.501
About what?

20:42.719 --> 20:44.243
I still got her clock.

20:46.375 --> 20:48.159
Well, give it here,

20:48.203 --> 20:50.466
because I paid $1,500
for this thing.

20:50.510 --> 20:52.076
JAY-BO:
Yo, man!

20:52.120 --> 20:54.557
You got my grandma's clock!

